rst Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Like   Jane   and   Joan  , a medieval variant of Old French <i>Je(h)anne</i>. Towards the end of the Middle Ages this form became largely confined to Scotland. In the 20th century it became more widely used in the English-speaking world and enjoyed a period of great popularity, but it is now out of fashion. Among numerous well-known and influential bearers are the British novelists  Jean Plaidy  (  Eleanor Hibbert ,  1910–93 ) and  Jean Rhys  (  Ella Gwendolen Rees Williams ,  1894–1979 ), British actress  Jean Simmons  (  1929–2010 ), and American-born actress  Jean Seberg  (  1938–79 ). It is also found as a variant spelling of the masculine name   Gene ."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."]},{"name":"Jeane","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Jean ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Jean de BRIENNE was born on 8 June 1170, in Brienne-le-Château, Aube, Grand Est, France. He married of Leon Berengeria from 1203 to 1230. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 27 March 1237, in Istanbul, Fatih, İstanbul, Türkiye, at the age of 66."},"et":{"8 JUN 1170–27 MAR 1237":"8. juuni 1170–27. märts 1237","1180–1237":"1180–1237","1172–1266":"1172–1266","1202–1296":"1202–1296","1227–1270":"1227–1270","1170–1237":"1170–1237","19 MAY 1222":"19. mai 1222","8 JUN 1170":"8. juuni 1170","ABT 1202":"umbes 1202","Abt 1227":"umbes 1227","1296":"1296","1172":"1172","1270":"1270","1170":"1170","1180":"1180","1227":"1227","1237":"1237","27 MAR 1237":"27. märts 1237","1202":"1202","BET 1203 AND 1230":"1203 kuni 1230","1266":"1266","BET 1204 AND 1266":"1204 kuni 1266","Constantinople,34126,Fatih,Istanbul,TURQUIE,":"Istanbul, Fatih, İstanbul, Türgi","Tolède,,Tolède,Castille-la Manche,Espagne,":"Toledo, Castilla-La Mancha, Hispaania","Brienne-le-Château,10064,Aube,Grand Est,FRANCE,":"Brienne-le-Château, Aube, Grand Est, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"8 JUN 1170–27 MAR 12